A conference of the **Fascist Party** was held at **Naples** on **October 24, 1922**. It was attended by about **40,000 armed volunteers**. In this conference, **Mussolini** announced that if his demands were not fulfilled, he would attack Rome with his volunteers. The demands put forward by Mussolini included the following:
*   Five members of the Fascist Party to be included in the Cabinet;
*   New elections to be announced;
*   The Government should act firmly on its foreign policy; and
*   Economic reforms to be implemented as early as possible.
